name: PhoneNumber

unions.name: NumberType
unions.comment: What kind of a number are we talking about? Fixed line? Mobile number? Pager number? etc.

aliases.name: Country
aliases.comment: Contains phone related metadata for a country
aliases.type: { id : String.String, countryCode : String.String, internationalPrefix : Maybe.Maybe String.String, nationalPrefix : Maybe.Maybe String.String, generalNumberPattern : Regex.Regex, numberTypes : List.List PhoneNumber.NumberTypeData }

aliases.name: NumberTypeData
aliases.comment:
Describes a NumberType with an example number, as well as a regex to validate if a given number is of
the set numberType
aliases.type: { numberType : PhoneNumber.NumberType, exampleNumber : String.String, pattern : Regex.Regex }

aliases.name: ValidationConfig
aliases.comment:
Pass this record to `valid` or `matches` to define how validation should occur.

Validation will occur against the default country as well as the list of other countries,
and validation will only occur against the list of number types. Providing a empty list of
number types might still succeed, as every country has a general number pattern that will be checked.

Any number that doesn't have an international prefix will be treated as if it belongs to the
default country.
aliases.type: { defaultCountry : PhoneNumber.Country, otherCountries : List.List PhoneNumber.Country, types : List.List PhoneNumber.NumberType }

values.name: anyType
values.comment:
A list of all number types. Use this if you don't care what kind of number something is,
but want to know if the number can belong to a certain country.

values.name: matches
values.comment:
Returns a list of tuples where the first element is a country that the number can belong to,
and the second list contains the different types the number can be. It's possible the the second
element is an empty list, as every country has a general number pattern that will be checked if the
number type cannot be determined.
values.type: PhoneNumber.ValidationConfig -> String.String -> List.List ( PhoneNumber.Country, List.List PhoneNumber.NumberType )

values.name: valid
values.comment: A simple test to see if the provided number matches anything provided by the validation config.

values.name: all
values.comment:
A list containing the metadata of all countries. You can use this as an easy way to create
a validation config. Keep in mind, though, that by using this list all metadata will be included in
your compiled asset file. A phone number can also, in the worst case, need to be compared against every
country when validating. For best results, create a list containing only the countries you're interested
in validating against.
